'''''Crusade in Europe''''' is a [[computer wargame]] published by [[MicroProse]] in 1985 for the [[Apple II]], [[Atari 8-bit computers]], [[Commodore 64]], and [[MS-DOS]]. It was designed by [[Sid Meier]] and Ed Bever.<ref name="giantlist">{{cite web |last1=Hague |first1=James |title=The Giant List of Classic Game Programmers |url=https://dadgum.com/giantlist/}}</ref>

==Gameplay==
''Crusade in Europe'' is a game in which its five available major operations include Normandy, Race for the Rhine, Market Garden, Bulge and the Campaign Scenario.<ref name="CGW24"/>

==Reception==
M. Evan Brooks reviewed the game for ''[[Computer Gaming World]]'', and stated that "''CIE'' offers five scenarios in one package, a bargain."<ref name="CGW24">{{cite magazine |last=Brooks |first=M. Evan |title=Microprose's Command Series |magazine=Computer Gaming World |date=Nov–Dec 1985 |volume=1 |issue=23 |pages=34–38}}</ref>

